SIMPLE: modernism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Modernism
<hw>Mod"ern*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Modern
practice; a thing of recent date; esp., a modern usage or mode of
expression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Certain methods and tendencies which, in Biblical
questions, apologetics, and the theory of dogma, in the endeavor to
reconcile the doctrines of the Roman Catholic Church with the
conclusions of modern science, replace the authority of the church by
purely subjective criteria; -- so called officially by Pope Pius
X.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Modernist</ent>⟦br⟧
